==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yuman
<hw>Yu"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Designating, or
pertaining to, an important linguistic stock of North American Indians
of the southwestern United States and northwestern Mexico, nearly all
agriculturists and adept potters and basket makers. Their usual dwelling
is the brush wikiup, and in their native state they wear little
clothing. The Yuma, Maricopa, Mohave, Walapi, and Yavapai are among the
chief tribes, all of fine physique.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yumas</ent>⟦br⟧
